:::summary
The Book of Mormon is a sacred volume of scripture and a keystone of Latter-day Saint faith. Its full title — *The Book of Mormon: Another Testament of Jesus Christ* — declares its central purpose: to testify that Jesus Christ is the Savior of the world. Translated by Joseph Smith through the gift and power of God from ancient golden plates, it records the history, prophecies, and teachings of peoples who inhabited the ancient Americas.
:::

